              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>MarTech covers the full marketing spectrum — content management, email, SEO, CRM, analytics, automation. AdTech specifically handles advertising: programmatic buying, demand-side platforms, ad exchanges, and real-time bidding. AdTech is a subset of MarTech focused exclusively on paid media execution and measurement.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How do you audit a MarTech stack?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>List every tool with its monthly cost, primary user, and primary function. Identify: (1) tools where no one could name the last time they used it, (2) tools with overlapping functionality, (3) tools not integrated with your CRM. Eliminate redundancies and disconnected tools. Teams typically save 15-25% of martech spend from a thorough annual audit.</p></div></div>
          </div>
